Gully Boy, directed by Zoya Akhtar, has been announced as India's official entry for Oscars 2020. The film, co-starring Alia Bhatt, Ranveer Singh and Siddhant Chaturvedi in lead roles, premiered at Berlin International Film Festival. After its release in theatres in February, the social media was flooded with positive reviews for the film. The news was shared by the film's producer Farhan Akhtar on social media. Farhan, in a tweet, wrote, "#GullyBoy has been selected as India’s official entry to the 92nd Oscar Awards. #apnatimeaayega.Thank you to the film federation and congratulations #Zoya @kagtireema @ritesh_sid @RanveerOfficial @aliaa08 @SiddhantChturvD @kalkikanmani & cast, crew and hip hop crew." #GullyBoy has been selected as India’s official entry to the 92nd Oscar Awards. #apnatimeaayega
Thank you to the film federation and congratulations #Zoya @kagtireema @ritesh_sid @RanveerOfficial @aliaa08 @SiddhantChturvD @kalkikanmani & cast, crew and hip hop crew. pic.twitter.com/Eyg02iETmG Soon after he shared the news on Twitter and Instagram, fans couldn't help but send congratulatory messages and good luck wishes to team Gully Boy. Many of them celebrated the movie and others pointed out how proud the film makes Indians feels. Amidst all the congratulatory messages, many Bollywood celebrities, too, poured in special messages for the film's team. From Hrithik Roshan, Dia Mirza, Karan Johar, Anubhav Sinha to Aditi Rao Hydari and Uday Chopra, many celebs posted good luck messages on social media. Check out reactions on Farhan's Instagram post: Karan Johar, who never fails to laud his peers on their achievements, wrote, "My absolute favourite film of the year is the official Indian entry for the OSCARS!!!! #GullyBoy all the way! Zoya Akhtar is my favourite Indian filmmaker! Well done boys @FarOutAkhtar@ritesh_sid get the gold statue home!!! So excited !! @aliaa08 @RanveerOfficial and the team!"  My absolute favourite film of the year is the official Indian entry for the OSCARS!!!! #GullyBoy all the way! Zoya Akhtar is my favourite Indian filmmaker! Well done boys @FarOutAkhtar @ritesh_sid get the gold statue home!!! So excited !! @aliaa08 @RanveerOfficial and the team! Filmmaker Alankrita Shrivastava wrote, "This is the BEST news ever. #GullyBoy India's entry to  #Oscars2020 Congratulations #ZoyaAkthar 
@RanveerOfficial@aliaa08 @ritesh_sid @FarOutAkhtar@kagtireema Please bring the Oscar home.." This is the BEST news ever. #GullyBoy India's entry to #Oscars2020Congratulations #ZoyaAkthar @RanveerOfficial @aliaa08 @ritesh_sid @FarOutAkhtar @kagtireema Please bring the Oscar home. Celebrating the announcement, Randeep Hooda wrote, "Truly deserved #GullyBoy #Oscars2020 #apnatimeaaega @RanveerOfficial @aliaa08 @FarOutAkhtar @ritesh_sid @ZoyaAkhtarOff." Truly deserved #GullyBoy #Oscars2020 #apnatimeaaega @RanveerOfficial @aliaa08 @FarOutAkhtar @ritesh_sid @ZoyaAkhtarOff https://t.co/1fHVKsowyr Filmmaker Anubhav Sinha, whose own film Article 15 was contending at the selection process, wished the team luck. The director tweeted, "Yayyyyyyy #GullyBoy go kill it!!!" Yayyyyyyy #GullyBoy go kill it!!! Uday Chopra, who has been away from the big screen wrote, "Congratulations!!!" Congratulations!!! Kalki Koechlin, who features in a key role in the film, wrote, "Woweeeeeeeee!!!!!!! That is just the best Saturday evening news!"  Woweeeeeeeee!!!!!!! That is just the best Saturday evening news! https://t.co/h5MRa2kQlrProducer Guneet Monga wrote, "From India to Oscars “Apna Time Aayega” #GULLYBOY by Zoya Akhtar congratulations @ZoyaAkhtarOff @ritesh_sid
@RanveerOfficial @aliaa08 @MrVijayVarma 2019 India’s entry to @TheAcademy." From India to Oscars “Apna Time Aayega” #GULLYBOY by Zoya Akhtar
